donot forget to add the requierments.txt file that has:
Flask==2.0.1

1. first pull the docker image from my account
docker pull sgadyahmed41/assignment-image

2.then build the image
docker build -t  assignment-image . 

3.now run the image
docker run -p 5000:5000 assignment-image

4.now test the api with the endpoints using /persons after the link
To test the GET /persons endpoint, send a GET request to http://localhost:5000/persons. You should receive a JSON response containing a list of persons.

To test the POST /persons endpoint, send a POST request to http://localhost:5000/persons with a JSON payload containing the person's data. You should receive a JSON response containing the person's data.

To test the GET /persons/{id} endpoint, send a GET request to http://localhost:5000/persons/{id} where {id} is the ID of the person you want to retrieve. You should receive a JSON response containing the person's data.

To test the PUT /persons/{id} endpoint, send a PUT request to http://localhost:5000/persons/{id} with a JSON payload containing the person's updated data. You should receive a JSON response containing the updated person's data.

To test the DELETE /persons/{id} endpoint, send a DELETE request to http://localhost:5000/persons/{id} where {id} is the ID of the person you want to delete. You should receive a JSON response indicating whether the deletion was successful or not.

